articles.author: Jacek Lepiarz
articles.title: Presidential election outcome a blow to Poland's government - DW
articles.description: Right-wing conservative historian and euroskeptic Karol Nawrocki has won the Polish presidential runoff by a whisker. The result is a bitter blow for Donald Tusk's pro-European government.
articles.content: Poland's State Election Commission announced on Monday morning that the right-wing conservative historian and euroskeptic Karol Nawrocki had received 50.89% of the vote in Sunday's presidential runof… [+5568 chars]
